Remote Impact JobsFor EmployersRemote Impact JobsFind a remote job in a mission-led organisation making positive change in the world.Subscribe to our newsletter:SubmitPopular Skillsremote react jobsremote python jobsremote frontend jobsremote backend jobsremote php jobsremote ios developer jobsremote linux jobsPopular Impact Areasclimate change remote jobseducation remote jobshealthcare remote jobsfood and agriculture remote jobsÂ© 2023 Remote Impact. All Rights Reserved.By continuing to use this site you accept our privacy and cookie policy.OKprops:pageProps:jobs:_id:64edb9d1b40b3f259cc341a3,id:5b957,company:ZOE,role:Engineering Manager - Technology,description:<div class=\section-wrapper page-full-width\u003e<div class=\section page-centered\ data-qa=\job-description\u003e<div><span style= ont-size: 18px\u003eWe are redefining how people approach their health</span></div><div><br></div><div>ZOE is combining scientific research at a scale never before imagined and cutting-edge AI to improve the health of millions. </div><div> </div><div>Created by the worldâs top scientists, our personalised nutrition program is radically reimagining a fundamental human need â eating well for your own body. Currently available in the US and the UK, having generated a waitlist of over 300,000, ZOE is already helping <a href=\https://www.trustpilot.com/review/joinzoe.com\ class=\postings-link\u003etens of thousands of ZOE members</a> adopt healthier habits and achieve their goals.</div><div> </div><div>We are also the team behind the popular COVID Symptom Study, which played a critical role in the fight against COVID in the UK and has now expanded to become the ZOE Health Study (ZHS). ZHS uses the power of community science to conduct large-scale research from the comfort of contributorsâ homes to understand health and prevent disease. Our collective work and expertise in biology, engineering, data science, and nutrition science has led to multiple breakthrough papers in leading scientific journals such as Nature Medicine, Science, The Lancet, and more.</div><div> </div><div>A remote-first, well-funded startup, we are backed by founders, investors, and entrepreneurs who have built multi-billion dollar technology companies. We are always looking for innovative thinkers and doers to join our team on a thrilling mission to tackle epic health problems that span the globe. Together, we can improve human health and touch millions of lives.</div><div> </div><div>We value inclusivity, transparency, ownership, open-mindedness and diversity. We are passionate about delivering great results and learning in the open. We want our teams to have the freedom to make long-term, high-impact decisions, and the well-being of our teammates and the people around us is a top priority.</div><div><br></div><div>Check out what life is like for our Engineers at our <a href=\https://www.notion.so/joinzoe/ZOE-Engineering-e9bdd71ce4714256adb72d588dc8234e\ class=\postings-link\u003eZOE Engineering</a> page</div><div><br></div><div><b>About ZOE Tech</b></div><div>ZOEs Technology teams are working on unique product challenges: building delightful user experiences, analysing data for millions of users, predicting food responses, integrating with labs, automating our logistics, or acquiring customers at scale.</div><div>We are always looking for innovative thinkers and doers to join our team. Together, we can improve human health and touch millions of lives.</div><div><br></div><div>We strive to make use of best practices, and believe in always choosing the right tool for the job. We move fast, gathering feedback from our (at least) daily deployments. We collaborate and learn together, building strong working relationships that help us to build a product to fulfil our mission to improve the health of millions. Find out more about our group on <a href=\https://joinzoe.notion.site/ZOE-Tech-e9bdd71ce4714256adb72d588dc8234e\ class=\postings-link\u003ezoe.tech</a></div><div><br></div><div><b>About the role</b></div><div>We are looking for technically minded people leaders who prioritise building a culture that enables their team to sustainably deliver at pace. You will partner with fellow engineers, product managers, data scientists, product designers and UX researchers to deliver meaningful customer impact and make ZOE a great place to work.</div></div><div class=\section page-centered\u003e<div><h3>Youll be</h3><ul class=\posting-requirements plain-list\u003e<ul><li>Leading a team of 3-6 engineers, focusing on outcome over output</li><li>Spending 40%-60% of your time deep in the code, leading by example on code and testing best practices. You are not afraid to dive into very technical conversations.</li><li>Challenging the team on scope or sequencing to deliver faster, while still decreasing technical debt. </li><li>Coaching, mentoring and developing high-performing engineers. </li><li>Ensuring high psychological safety, where collaboration and equal voice are cornerstones of the team culture. </li><li>Partnering with other engineering managers on cross cutting initiatives like hiring or onboarding.</li><li>Building good relationships with your stakeholders to establish a roadmap that delivers value to our members.</li><li>Releasing small changes regularly to get fast feedback from our users</li><li>Optimising application performance and ensuring smooth user experience across different platforms and devices.</li><li>Providing constructive feedback through code reviews and regular 1:1s</li><li>Staying updated with the latest trends and advancements to proactively bring new ideas and approaches to the team.</li><li>Thinking longer term when solving challenges to ensure we build scalable, maintainable, observable systems that will continue to meet our needs as we grow.</li></ul></ul></div></div><div class=\section page-centered\u003e<div><h3>We think youll be great if you</h3><ul class=\posting-requirements plain-list\u003e<ul><li>Are experienced in leading a distributed full-stack team, in a fast pace environment.</li><li>Are someone who takes ownership and is comfortable with ambiguity. You provide clarity and make things happen.</li><li>Have the ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams and communicate technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.</li><li>A servant leader who leads by example, finding opportunities for others to grow and shine.</li><li>Someone who enjoys stepping back and seeing problems from a different perspective in order to find innovative solutions.</li><li>Have great communication skills, both verbal and in writing.</li><li>Have an appetite to work closely with our product team to test and release new ideas fast.</li><li>Have experience with paired programming.</li><li>Are data-driven. You challenge teams to measure impact and demonstrate added value.</li><li>Have strong problem-solving and analytical skills.</li><li>Pay close attention to detail and a commitment to delivering high-quality code.</li></ul></ul></div></div><div class=\section page-centered\u003e<div><h3>We will also appreciate if you have any of the following</h3><ul class=\posting-requirements plain-list\u003e<ul><li>An incredible growth mindset. You read books, watch talks, listen to podcasts and are never afraid to try new things.</li><li>Experience building mobile apps.</li><li>Experience with scalability (backend, data pipelines).</li><li>Experience working with Support teams, and understand best practices for handling Support at scale.</li><li>Experience working with payments and finance.</li><li>Experience with state management libraries (e.g., Redux, MobX) and UI component libraries (e.g., Material-UI, Ant Design).</li><li>Experience deploying machine learning in production.</li></ul></ul></div></div><div class=\section page-centered\u003e<div><h3>The interview process</h3><ul class=\posting-requirements plain-list\u003e<ul><li>Intro to ZOE with a Talent Partner (30 mins).</li><li>Intro with our VP of Engineering or Senior Engineering Manager (30mins).</li><li>Technical Interview &amp; Systems Design (90 mins). As part of this stage, we will ask you to teach us something technical asynchronously (text or video) to assess your ability to go in-depth and communicate.</li><li>Behavioural interviews with a Senior Engineering manager (60mins) and VP of Engineering (60 mins).</li><li>Meet a senior stakeholder outside of Technology (30mins) and meet a founder (30mins).</li></ul></ul></div></div><!--2022-11-28 GOLD-2535 Remove payTransparencyV1 when feature flag is fully removed--><div class=\section page-centered\ data-qa=\closing-description\u003e<div>Check out what life is like for our Engineers at our <a href=\https://www.notion.so/joinzoe/ZOE-Engineering-e9bdd71ce4714256adb72d588dc8234e\ class=\postings-link\u003eZOE Engineering</a> page</div><div><br></div><div><span style= ont-size: 18px\u003eThis isnt for you if:</span></div><div>ð Our mission to help people live healthier lives doesnât excite you.</div><div>ð You arenât comfortable with ambiguity, or thinking from first principles.</div><div>ð You donât enjoy working in a fast paced environment.</div><div>ð You arenât happy taking an MVP approach and doing whatâs good enough for now</div><div> </div><div><span style= ont-size: 18px\u003eWhy youâll love it here</span></div><div>Discover our values and our career page to find out more.</div><div>â­ Youll be energised by testimonials of members who had life-changing experiences</div><div>â­ Youâll be surrounded by the most friendly, supportive colleagues you can imagine. We have assembled the sharpest minds from diverse backgrounds</div><div>â­ As we grow, so will you! ZOEâs fast-paced, challenging environment offers you great opportunities for professional development, supported by a yearly growth budget (Â£150/â¬175/$200 no question asked budget and up to Â£750/â¬875/$1,000 with your managers approval).</div><div>â­ We embraced flexible and distributed working and keep everyone informed through our transparent culture. You will be in complete control of your work environment. We have an office open to you, but you are never required to use it. You can choose whether to come in and meet colleagues face to face, or be fully remote</div><div>â­ Switching off is important! At ZOE, we understand that to do your best work, you also need to be able to relax and connect with your colleagues. Enjoy our fun virtual and face-to-face social events, supported by a $70/month social budget</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><span style= ont-size: 18px\u003eWhat we can offer you: </span></div><div><b>Remote-first</b> - work from home, pop into our LondoBoston offices, or work within the EU; you have flexibility to choose your own place of work and work flexibly</div><div><b>Stock options</b> - we want everyone to be rewarded for contribution to our growth </div><div><b>Paid time-off</b> - on top of any national / bank holidays, you get 28 days off (25 plus 1 life-event and 2 company-wide reset days) </div><div><b>Enhanced parental leave</b> - Enhanced parental leave, family planning and pregnancy/adoption loss leave - adding on to the statutory offering, we know how important it is to be supportive at times that matter </div><div><b>Private healthcare</b> and <b>life assurance</b> - flexible options to choose what fits </div><div><b>Health and wellbeing</b> - ZOE nutrition product, Employee Assistance Program, Spill mental health support, Cycle to Work, yoga and more </div><div><b>Pension</b> - paying monthly and offering flexibility to top your pension up </div><div>Allocated social, WFH and Growth (L&amp;D) budgets from the day you join</div><div>Plenty of <b>learning and social opportunities </b></div><div><br></div></div><div class=\section page-centered last-section-apply\ data-qa= tn-apply-bottom\u003e<a class=\postings-btn template-btn-submit hex-color\ data-qa=\show-page-apply\ href=\https://jobs.lever.co/joinzoe/fcfcbc7c-9ea3-4977-bf9f-2685f876d97a/apply\u003eApply for this job</a></div></div>,location:UK/EU or compatible timezone (Remote),impact:sdg3,link:https://jobs.lever.co/joinzoe/fcfcbc7c-9ea3-4977-bf9f-2685f876d97a,slug:engineering-manager-technology-zoe-5b957,date:2023-08-29T09:26:40.289Z,tags:backend,redux,product team,systems design,salaryMin:0,salaryMax:0,approved:false,__N_SSP:true,page:/jobs/slug,query:slug:engineering-manager-technology-zoe-5b957,buildId:LqM2mYzRohf_0wBi8sEjq,isFallback:false,gssp:true,scriptLoader:id:ga,strategy:lazyOnload,src:https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-XZG534BGMN,id:ga2,strategy:lazyOnload,children:
